It is a TypeScript implementation whose tool, resource, and prompt interface is
designed to be compatible with the uk-legal-mcp project, and which incorporates
and adapts portions of that MIT-licensed project — including OSCOLA citation
regex patterns — as acknowledged below. It was written against the Model Context
Protocol TypeScript SDK (@modelcontextprotocol/sdk). It targets publicly
available UK legal data sources (The National Archives Find Case Law,
legislation.gov.uk, the UK Parliament APIs, and GOV.UK/HMRC); those sources and
their data are the property of their respective owners and are used under their
own terms.

Third-party open-source packages used at runtime (declared in package.json)
remain under their own licences, held in each package's distribution.


